---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="BridgeAIChat Quickstart" description="Get BridgeAIChat running across a control host and one agent device.">
  <section class="surface">
    <div class="eyebrow">Quickstart</div>
    <h1>Bring up the beta in three moves.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      The beta path is intentionally simple: run the gateway with Tailscale API credentials, enter your tailnet in the
      UI, and connect one agent device over Tailscale.
    </p>
    <div class="status section"><strong>Beta note:</strong> Codex and Claude both work in the current beta. Claude should use <code>direct: true</code> and <code>--dangerously-skip-permissions</code> in <code>agent.yaml</code>.</div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap step-list">
    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">1</div>
      <p class="mini-title">Start the control host</p>
      <pre>export TAILSCALE_CLIENT_ID=tsid_xxx
export TAILSCALE_CLIENT_SECRET=tssecret_xxx
export TAILSCALE_API_BASE=https://api.tailscale.com/api/v2
export APP_URL=http://localhost:8080

./bridge-gateway</pre>
      <p class="muted">Use the <code>bridge-ai-app</code> release archive or a local build. The gateway serves the UI on <code>http://localhost:8080</code>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">2</div>
      <p class="mini-title">Open the UI and connect your tailnet</p>
      <pre>http://localhost:8080

Continue with Tailscale
example.ts.net</pre>
      <p class="muted">The browser stores the selected tailnet in the session, then loads devices from the Tailscale API.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <div class="step-number">3</div>
      <p class="mini-title">Install one agent on another machine</p>
      <pre>export BRIDGE_AGENT_GATEWAY_URL=ws://your-control-host:8080/agent
bash install-agent.sh
./bridge-agent -config ./agent.yaml</pre>
      <p class="muted">Once the machine is reachable in Tailscale, it should show as <code>Agent Missing</code> first and switch to <code>Connected</code> after the agent comes online.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-gap grid two">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Required Gateway Env</div>
      <h2>What the control host needs</h2>
      <pre>TAILSCALE_CLIENT_ID=tsid_xxx
TAILSCALE_CLIENT_SECRET=tssecret_xxx
TAILSCALE_API_BASE=https://api.tailscale.com/api/v2
APP_URL=http://localhost:8080</pre>
      <p>These credentials let the gateway exchange a client-credentials token and list devices for the tailnet entered in the UI.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <div class="eyebrow">Expected Device States</div>
      <h2>What you should see</h2>
      <ul class="list tight">
        <li><code>Connected</code>: the machine is online in Tailscale and the Bridge agent is connected</li>
        <li><code>Agent Missing</code>: the machine is online in Tailscale but no Bridge agent is connected yet</li>
        <li><code>Offline</code>: the machine is currently offline in Tailscale</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
